thetic or metaphysical pursuits is a constant theme of Nabokov's and that the tension between technique and content is itself a key to his fiction. Written with verve and precision, Toker's book begins with Pnin and follows the circular pattern that is one of her subject's own favored devices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAmerican literature. 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aSoviet & East European History. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Modern / 20th Century .2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066749340uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501707049?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501707049zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501707049/original  a978-3-11-053617-1 Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  a978-3-11-066749-3 Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA